What makes the Linksys WRT54GL famous?
  I know that they are popular I'm not sure about famous but they are very reliable and can also be used with opensource firmware such as MikrotiK equipment but with a name backed by Cisco.

Given it’s age, why do people continue to buy the Linksys WRT54GL?
  Due to the ability to use open source firmware and also because of reliability and of course name recognition...ie my mentor showed me how to set this up using X equipment and said its the best...
then they follow suit.

What does the “WRT54GL” stand for in the name?
  I had to look this up on the manufacture web page WRT is Wireless Router and 54 is 54Mbps and the G is for the standart it used 802.11G

What did Linksys sell before routers?
  They are actually a branch off of Cisco when they bought them and later sold again to Belkin and used to make connectors from printers to PC....now much easier and cheaper solutions are available.

When did Linksys preview their first consumer router?
  1990

Who suggested to name it a “router”?
  The International Networking Working Group or INWG but unofficially Bill Gates 

What happened when Cisco replaced the Linux-based firmware with the VxWorks platform?
  They made alot of people upset and eventually after a lawsuit reseased the L version with linux and provided open source.

Why doesn’t the WRT54GL model need to be modified to abide by the new FCC rules?
  The new rules apply to the 5GHz band

Does the WRT54GL model still get updates from Linksys?
  The update on their site shows 01/22/2016 version 4.30.18 build 6
